00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:41,080
and certainly don't stare at the sun.

564
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:43,040
Never force yourself to look at any light,

565
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,140
sunlight or otherwise,

566
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:46,440
that's so bright that it's painful to look at.

567
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:49,000
So if it's comfortable for you to look directly at the sun

568
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,200
and just blink every once in a while

569
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,300
and you can do that without any pain or discomfort

570
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:54,320
or watering of the eyes, please do that.

571
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:56,880
You're getting a lot of photons into your eyes

572
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,400
and they're transmitting that to your brain

573
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,920
and your brain to the rest of your body and on and on.

574
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,380
However, if you find it uncomfortable

575
00:22:02,380 --> 00:22:03,720
to look directly at the sun,

576
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:06,560
in that case, what you'll want to do is offset your gaze

577
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:08,880
to 10 or 20 degrees, which is nerd speak

578
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,160
for just a little bit to the right

579
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:11,560
or a little bit to the left

580
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:15,000
and get the sunlight into your eyes indirectly.

581
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,480
Okay, and I often also get asked,

582
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,200
well, can I stand in the shade while I do this?

