00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:05,740
have these exact same circuits and pathways

604
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:07,200
for setting their circadian rhythm.

605
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,780
So it's great for them too.

606
00:23:08,780 --> 00:23:11,520
Now there are also clear and documented benefits

607
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:12,620
for mood and mental health

608
00:23:12,620 --> 00:23:14,020
to getting bright light in your eyes,

609
00:23:14,020 --> 00:23:16,340
ideally from sunlight throughout the day,

610
00:23:16,340 --> 00:23:17,600
as much as you safely can.

611
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,180
Please don't get sunburned,

612
00:23:19,180 --> 00:23:22,500
don't get cataracts by getting too much sunlight,

613
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:24,580
but getting outdoors and getting sunlight in your eyes

614
00:23:24,580 --> 00:23:27,140
during your lunch break or a walk here and there,

615
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:30,060
or if you have to remain indoors during the day,

616
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:33,280
getting the lights in that environment as bright as possible

617
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:35,120
as is safely possible, I should say,

618
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:37,800
is known to improve mood and mental health.

619
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:38,640
Why?

620
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:41,240
Well, because there's a special so-called opsin

621
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:43,900
within the cells of your eyes called melanopsin

622
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:47,580
that doesn't respond to the same differences in color

623
00:23:47,580 --> 00:23:50,220
that are present in sunlight in the morning and the evening,

624
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:53,540
but rather responds to the overall brightness of light.

625
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:56,180
So very bright lights, either from artificial sources

626
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:58,660
or ideally from sunlight, activate these cells

627
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:01,180
and these cells project these little wires,

628
00:24:01,180 --> 00:24:03,820
we call axons, into specific parts of the brain

629
00:24:03,820 --> 00:24:06,980
that improve your mood and feelings of wellbeing.

630
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:10,660
So I can't give you a specific number

631
00:24:10,660 --> 00:24:12,680
of five minutes a day or 10 minutes a day.

632
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,300
Just get as much light in your eyes,

633
00:24:14,300 --> 00:24:16,260
ideally from sunlight throughout the day,

634
00:24:16,260 --> 00:24:17,740
as is safe for you,

635
00:24:17,740 --> 00:24:19,260
meaning where you're not getting sunburned

636
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:20,820
and you're not damaging your retina.

637
00:24:20,820 --> 00:24:23,120
And if you want to know if you're damaging your retina,

638
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:25,820
well, anytime you have to blink or turn away from light

639
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:26,860
because it's really bright,

640
00:24:26,860 --> 00:24:28,900
that's a signal that the light is too bright.

641
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,580
So while you want to place yourself into bright environments,

642
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:33,620
you don't want to place yourself into any environment

643
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:35,620
so bright that it's painful to be in.

644
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:38,460
Okay, so use that as a metric and you should be just fine.

645
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:41,060
And the last point about light for mood and mental health

646
00:24:41,060 --> 00:24:42,900
is a relatively recent theme

647
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:44,860
that's emerging from the scientific literature

648
00:24:44,860 --> 00:24:47,660
and that really was driven home by a recent study

649
00:24:47,660 --> 00:24:49,260
that I mentioned a little bit earlier in the episode.

650
00:24:49,260 --> 00:24:51,540
This is the study published in Nature Mental Health,

651
00:24:51,540 --> 00:24:54,900
showing that darkness during a particular stage

652
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:56,460
of your 24 hour cycle,

653
00:24:56,460 --> 00:24:58,260
your so-called circadian rhythm,

654
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:02,300
is also very beneficial for mood and mental health.

655
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:04,720
And it's beneficial for mood and mental health

656
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:09,060
in a way that is independent from light and from sleep.

657
00:25:09,060 --> 00:25:10,260
Now, what do I mean by that?

658
00:25:10,260 --> 00:25:11,940
Okay, well, there are a number of different ways

659
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:13,180
that this can be examined,

660
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:16,980
but in this particular study, which I like oh so much,

661
00:25:16,980 --> 00:25:19,580
entitled Day and Night Light Exposure

662
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:21,980
are Associated with Psychiatric Disorders,

663
00:25:21,980 --> 00:25:25,900
an objective light study in more than 85,000 people.

664
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:30,060
What the researchers did is they analyzed how much light

665
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:33,780
and or dark people were getting across the 24 hour cycle

666
00:25:33,780 --> 00:25:36,860
and correlated that with mental health outcomes,

667
00:25:36,860 --> 00:25:39,220
looking at a range of different mental health challenges,

668
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:41,900
including bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, depression,

669
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:43,820
PTSD, and much more.

670
00:25:43,820 --> 00:25:46,300
And I'll go into this study in a lot of detail

671
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:47,220
in a future episode,

672
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:48,580
cause it's such an important study

673
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:51,180
with so many gems within it that we should all know about.

674
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:53,680
But one of the key things from this study

675
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:58,180
is that the positive effects of daytime sunlight exposure

676
00:25:58,180 --> 00:26:02,340
and the positive effects of nighttime dark exposure,

677
00:26:02,340 --> 00:26:04,940
that means of course the absence of light,

678
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:07,300
are independent of one another.

679
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:10,980
Put differently, making sure that you're in very dim

680
00:26:10,980 --> 00:26:13,640
to completely dark environments

681
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:16,760
for a continuous six to eight hours

682
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:19,620
within every 24 hours circadian cycle

683
00:26:19,620 --> 00:26:23,040
is correlated with much better mental health outcomes.

684
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,720
In other words, we shouldn't just think about

685
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:28,080
the presence of light in the morning

686
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:30,040
and throughout the day as positive for mental health.

687
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,160
That's all true, it's absolutely true.

688
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:33,800
And this study further verifies that,

689
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,280
but that's been known for some time,

690
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:38,200
indeed decades from the scientific research.

691
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,420
And of course it's been known for thousands of years

692
00:26:40,420 --> 00:26:42,080
intuitively and subjectively

693
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:45,380
without detailed scientific measurement.

694
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:46,880
But in addition to that,

695
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:51,160
this study shows that people who stay in very dim

696
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:55,560
to dark environments for eight hours every 24 hours,

697
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:57,920
or I should say approximately eight hours

698
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,900
in every 24 hour cycle,

699
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:03,080
they benefit from improved mood and mental health outcomes

700
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,740
in a way that's independent of how much light they're getting

701
00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:09,300
and independent of how much sleep they are getting.

702
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:11,320
The point is this, the time when you wake up,

