00:50:32,220 --> 00:50:34,100
and indeed form a critical component

1307
00:50:35,020 --> 00:50:36,420
of what Dr. Paul Conti referred to

1308
00:50:36,420 --> 00:50:39,300
as the first principles of self-care

1309
00:50:39,300 --> 00:50:43,220
is that those six pillars establish a milieu

1310
00:50:43,220 --> 00:50:46,260
that is an environment of neurochemicals,

1311
00:50:46,260 --> 00:50:49,260
including neuromodulators such as dopamine, serotonin,

1312
00:50:49,260 --> 00:50:51,980
epinephrine, norepinephrine, acetylcholine,

1313
00:50:51,980 --> 00:50:55,380
and other neurochemicals as well, as well as hormones,

1314
00:50:55,380 --> 00:50:58,460
testosterone, estrogen, prolactin, cortisol,

1315
00:50:58,460 --> 00:51:01,820
and immune molecules and on and on

1316
00:51:01,820 --> 00:51:05,420
that lead to a high degree of predictability

1317
00:51:05,420 --> 00:51:07,300
in your brain and nervous system.

1318
00:51:07,300 --> 00:51:08,380
Now, what do I mean by that?

1319
00:51:08,380 --> 00:51:11,260
Why would predictability be such a key component

1320
00:51:11,260 --> 00:51:12,580
of mood and mental health?

1321
00:51:12,580 --> 00:51:14,420
Is it really just about knowing that you're going

1322
00:51:14,420 --> 00:51:16,380
to feel energized in the early part of the day

1323
00:51:16,380 --> 00:51:18,020
and tired at the end of the day?

1324
00:51:18,020 --> 00:51:19,060
Now, that might be part of it,

1325
00:51:19,060 --> 00:51:21,300
but that's not the major takeaway.

1326
00:51:21,300 --> 00:51:24,620
The major takeaway is that as Dr. Lisa Feldman Barrett,

1327
00:51:24,620 --> 00:51:27,180
so aptly pointed out, your brain

1328
00:51:27,180 --> 00:51:29,260
and indeed your entire nervous system

1329
00:51:29,260 --> 00:51:31,180
has a couple of major jobs,

1330
00:51:31,180 --> 00:51:33,020
has the job of regulating your breathing

1331
00:51:33,020 --> 00:51:34,980
and your heart rate, et cetera.

1332
00:51:34,980 --> 00:51:37,260
It also has the job of regulating your thinking

1333
00:51:37,260 --> 00:51:38,940
and your planning and your memory.

1334
00:51:38,940 --> 00:51:41,180
Those are the jobs of the brain and nervous system

1335
00:51:41,180 --> 00:51:42,780
that we normally hear about.

1336
00:51:42,780 --> 00:51:44,900
But if we think about the more macro jobs

1337
00:51:44,900 --> 00:51:48,380
that the brain has, the key function of the brain,

1338
00:51:48,380 --> 00:51:49,940
certainly the parts of the brain

1339
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:52,020
that are more recently evolved,

1340
00:51:52,020 --> 00:51:54,620
the ones involved in thinking and planning, et cetera,

1341
00:51:54,620 --> 00:51:57,740
are really involved in generating predictions,

1342
00:51:57,740 --> 00:52:00,300
predictions about what's going to happen next

1343
00:52:00,300 --> 00:52:02,220
and whether or not you're going to be prepared

1344
00:52:02,220 --> 00:52:03,740
for what's going to happen next.

1345
00:52:03,740 --> 00:52:06,060
And indeed, Dr. Lisa Feldman Barrett

1346
00:52:06,060 --> 00:52:08,420
also beautifully illustrated this model

1347
00:52:08,420 --> 00:52:12,340
of the brain as regulating a brain-body budget

1348
00:52:12,340 --> 00:52:16,980
and moods and a related topic, which she called affect.

1349
00:52:16,980 --> 00:52:19,300
Okay, I'll explain what affect is in a moment.

1350
00:52:19,300 --> 00:52:23,060
Setting the stage for being able to better predict

1351
00:52:23,060 --> 00:52:24,620
what's going to happen next

1352
00:52:24,620 --> 00:52:28,660
and therefore regulating your mood in the moment.

1353
00:52:28,660 --> 00:52:30,620
Let's just take a moment and explore that statement

1354
00:52:30,620 --> 00:52:32,300
in a little bit more detail.

1355
00:52:32,300 --> 00:52:33,500
Essentially what she was saying

1356
00:52:33,500 --> 00:52:35,420
and what I'm now again saying

1357
00:52:35,420 --> 00:52:38,620
is that your brain and body go through different states.

1358
00:52:38,620 --> 00:52:42,220
Your state at a given moment can be labeled as your affect.

1359
00:52:42,220 --> 00:52:44,140
Your affect includes a lot of different things,

1360
00:52:44,140 --> 00:52:46,580
including levels of autonomic arousal,

1361
00:52:46,580 --> 00:52:48,580
levels of hormones, levels of trans mirrors,

1362
00:52:48,580 --> 00:52:49,740
all of that stuff.

1363
00:52:49,740 --> 00:52:52,660
But it falls under the umbrella of affect.

1364
00:52:52,660 --> 00:52:57,500
Affect essentially sets the stage for particular emotions

1365
00:52:57,500 --> 00:53:00,300
to be more likely or less likely to emerge.

1366
00:53:00,300 --> 00:53:02,860
So emotion and affect aren't the same thing.

1367
00:53:02,860 --> 00:53:04,620
Affect is a bit more general.

1368
00:53:04,620 --> 00:53:07,180
It sort of undergirds the possibility

1369
00:53:07,180 --> 00:53:09,540
of having certain moods like feeling elated,

1370
00:53:09,540 --> 00:53:12,540
happy or sad or depressed.

1371
00:53:12,540 --> 00:53:14,380
It really sets the general stage

1372
00:53:14,380 --> 00:53:17,220
for different types of specific emotions,

1373
00:53:17,220 --> 00:53:19,380
even highly specific emotions.

1374
00:53:19,380 --> 00:53:22,980
So in that way, when you're taking care of the big six,

1375
00:53:22,980 --> 00:53:26,380
when you're tending to these six pillars on a regular basis,

1376
00:53:26,380 --> 00:53:28,780
and I should point out that we really want to tend

1377
00:53:28,780 --> 00:53:31,060
to those six pillars every single day

1378
00:53:31,060 --> 00:53:33,300
or every single 24 hours,

1379
00:53:33,300 --> 00:53:35,820
we really need to make those a regular investment

1380
00:53:35,820 --> 00:53:37,940
to the extent that we can.

1381
00:53:37,940 --> 00:53:41,180
When we do that, we create a neurochemical

1382
00:53:41,180 --> 00:53:44,500
and a neural milieu that allows the brain

1383
00:53:44,500 --> 00:53:47,180
to be in a better predictive state.

1384
00:53:47,180 --> 00:53:51,220
It allows the brain to give rise to certain affects,

1385
00:53:51,220 --> 00:53:54,380
spelled A-F-F-E-C-T-S,

1386
00:53:54,380 --> 00:53:57,340
so affects that lead to certain emotions

1387
00:53:57,340 --> 00:54:00,260
being more or less likely to occur.

1388
00:54:00,260 --> 00:54:03,020
Put very simply, when we're tending to those six pillars

1389
00:54:03,020 --> 00:54:06,420
on a regular basis, we feel better more generally,

1390
00:54:06,420 --> 00:54:10,060
and therefore the emotions that we tend to have

1391
00:54:10,060 --> 00:54:11,060
under different conditions,

1392
00:54:11,060 --> 00:54:13,260
even conditions of a difficult interaction

1393
00:54:13,260 --> 00:54:15,460
with a coworker or with a family member,

1394
00:54:15,460 --> 00:54:18,420
tend to be more positive than if we are not tending

1395
00:54:18,420 --> 00:54:19,900
to those six pillars.

1396
00:54:19,900 --> 00:54:22,580
Now, in some sense, that's sort of a duh statement.

1397
00:54:22,580 --> 00:54:24,020
For instance, if you're sleep deprived,

1398
00:54:24,020 --> 00:54:25,740
if you're not fed well,

1399
00:54:25,740 --> 00:54:27,340
like you haven't eaten in a few hours,

1400
00:54:27,340 --> 00:54:29,460
of course, you're going to be more irritable,

1401
00:54:29,460 --> 00:54:30,740
you're going to be more reactive,

1402
00:54:30,740 --> 00:54:33,460
you are going to be more emotionally labile.

1403
00:54:33,460 --> 00:54:34,620
But sleep and nutrition

1404
00:54:34,620 --> 00:54:37,180
are just two of those six core pillars.

1405
00:54:37,180 --> 00:54:38,900
When we talk about those core pillars

1406
00:54:38,900 --> 00:54:40,900
and the necessity for tending to them

1407
00:54:40,900 --> 00:54:43,540
on a regular, every 24-hour basis,

1408
00:54:43,540 --> 00:54:44,980
what we're really talking about

1409
00:54:44,980 --> 00:54:47,500
is creating a milieu within our brain and nervous system

1410
00:54:47,500 --> 00:54:50,500
that allows the nervous system to do what it does best,

1411
00:54:50,500 --> 00:54:53,500
and in fact, what its main job is to do,

1412
00:54:53,500 --> 00:54:55,620
which is to predict what's going to happen next.

1413
00:54:55,620 --> 00:54:57,900
Because as Lisa Feldman Barrett pointed out,

1414
00:54:57,900 --> 00:55:01,180
emotions are really context-dependent states

1415
00:55:01,180 --> 00:55:05,220
that allow us to navigate not just our present circumstances,

1416
00:55:05,220 --> 00:55:08,580
but they are our nervous system and brain's best guess

1417
00:55:08,580 --> 00:55:12,300
about the circumstances that we are soon going to encounter.

1418
00:55:12,300 --> 00:55:13,740
Now, I don't offer you all of that

1419
00:55:13,740 --> 00:55:17,460
as kind of a bunch of a tangled mess of nerd speak

1420
00:55:17,460 --> 00:55:18,300
to confuse you.

1421
00:55:18,300 --> 00:55:21,140
What I'm saying is that by tending to those six core pillars,

1422
00:55:21,140 --> 00:55:25,340
you are shifting the likely affects that you will experience

1423
00:55:25,340 --> 00:55:27,980
and therefore the likely emotions that you will experience.

1424
00:55:27,980 --> 00:55:29,540
So you're biasing your whole system

1425
00:55:29,540 --> 00:55:33,420
towards more positive affect and more positive emotions,

1426
00:55:33,420 --> 00:55:36,540
regardless of what your life circumstances happen to be

1427
00:55:36,540 --> 00:55:38,500
and the stressors that you encounter.

1428
00:55:38,500 --> 00:55:40,300
And indeed, you also are including

1429
00:55:40,300 --> 00:55:42,700
that six pillar of stress control.

1430
00:55:42,700 --> 00:55:44,540
So when those stressors arrive,

1431
00:55:44,540 --> 00:55:47,100
you'll be better able to navigate them.

1432
00:55:47,100 --> 00:55:49,380
Now, this view of emotion regulation,

1433
00:55:49,380 --> 00:55:51,020
of mood and mental health,

1434
00:55:51,060 --> 00:55:53,220
is certainly not a novel concept.

1435
00:55:53,220 --> 00:55:55,820
People have talked about the physiological regulation of mood

1436
00:55:55,820 --> 00:55:58,540
from the time of William James and even earlier.

1437
00:55:58,540 --> 00:56:00,420
It's been a long-standing question, for instance,

1438
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:02,700
or debate in psychology and philosophy.

1439
00:56:02,700 --> 00:56:06,140
Do we feel anxiety in our body and then label it as anxiety,

1440
00:56:06,140 --> 00:56:09,620
or do we feel anxiety in our mind and then our body follows?

1441
00:56:09,620 --> 00:56:10,900
That's been a long-standing debate

1442
00:56:10,900 --> 00:56:13,380
and frankly, there's evidence on both sides,

1443
00:56:13,380 --> 00:56:14,700
which leads me to the conclusion,

1444
00:56:14,700 --> 00:56:16,700
I think most neurobiologists and psychologists

1445
00:56:16,700 --> 00:56:19,220
to the conclusion that those things are interrelated

1446
00:56:19,220 --> 00:56:22,020
in a way that we can't really dissociate them completely

1447
00:56:22,020 --> 00:56:23,340
at any level, right?

1448
00:56:23,340 --> 00:56:24,340
When your heart rate goes up

1449
00:56:24,340 --> 00:56:26,140
and you start breathing faster,

1450
00:56:26,140 --> 00:56:27,580
if I were to induce that state in you,

1451
00:56:27,580 --> 00:56:30,620
you'd probably interpret that as feeling anxious.

1452
00:56:30,620 --> 00:56:31,460
In addition to that,

1453
00:56:31,460 --> 00:56:32,980
something can make you anxious

1454
00:56:32,980 --> 00:56:34,740
before your heart rate and breathing increases

1455
00:56:34,740 --> 00:56:36,180
and then your heart rate and breathing increases.

1456
00:56:36,180 --> 00:56:38,340
So no need to tease those apart.

1457
00:56:38,340 --> 00:56:40,140
But if you think about the brain,

1458
00:56:40,140 --> 00:56:42,100
in large part as a prediction machine

1459
00:56:42,100 --> 00:56:44,660
and your brain as a metabolic regulator,

1460
00:56:44,660 --> 00:56:47,180
it's trying to decide which organs need resources.

1461
00:56:47,180 --> 00:56:49,820
How much resource can I dedicate to thinking,

1462
00:56:49,820 --> 00:56:53,300
to creativity, to enjoying social interaction,

1463
00:56:53,300 --> 00:56:55,260
to paying attention to what somebody else is saying

1464
00:56:55,260 --> 00:56:57,340
as opposed to what's going on inside my body?

1465
00:56:57,340 --> 00:56:59,140
All of those major functions of the brain

1466
00:56:59,140 --> 00:57:01,820
as they relate to affect and emotions

1467
00:57:01,820 --> 00:57:03,940
are going to be best supported,

1468
00:57:03,940 --> 00:57:06,900
that is biased toward positive mood,

1469
00:57:06,900 --> 00:57:10,060
positive affect, positive emotions,

1470
00:57:10,060 --> 00:57:13,300
and therefore positive mental health outcomes

1471
00:57:13,300 --> 00:57:15,580
when we're tending to those six pillars.

1472
00:57:15,580 --> 00:57:17,940
Dr. Lisa Feldman Barrett referred to that whole process

1473
00:57:17,940 --> 00:57:21,180
as the brain regulating a brain body budget.

1474
00:57:21,180 --> 00:57:23,060
And she had beautiful analogies for that budget.

1475
00:57:23,060 --> 00:57:24,860
And that's what led to the description

1476
00:57:24,860 --> 00:57:27,940
of social interactions as either generating savings

1477
00:57:27,940 --> 00:57:31,300
or being neutral or generating a taxed feeling,

1478
00:57:31,300 --> 00:57:33,140
literally taxing that brain body budget.

1479
00:57:33,140 --> 00:57:34,100
And I love that concept.

1480
00:57:34,100 --> 00:57:35,700
And it's one that you can keep in mind.

1481
00:57:35,700 --> 00:57:38,620
And indeed we can inject a lot of specificity

1482
00:57:38,620 --> 00:57:41,780
into this whole process of improving mood and mental health

1483
00:57:41,780 --> 00:57:43,380
through specific protocols.

1484
00:57:43,380 --> 00:57:44,820
If you simply remember,

1485
00:57:44,820 --> 00:57:49,140
if you make a daily investment in the six core pillars,

1486
00:57:49,140 --> 00:57:51,860
you are building up that brain body budget.

1487
00:57:51,860 --> 00:57:55,740
You will have more energetic resources to spend

1488
00:57:55,740 --> 00:57:58,620
on whatever life circumstances come your way.

1489
00:57:58,620 --> 00:58:01,500
Now, before we move into a discussion about protocols

1490
00:58:01,500 --> 00:58:03,940
for how to better understand your life narrative

1491
00:58:03,940 --> 00:58:06,700
to enhance your sense of self and confidence

1492
00:58:06,700 --> 00:58:08,620
and things of that theme,

1493
00:58:08,620 --> 00:58:11,300
I briefly want to mention that,

1494
00:58:11,300 --> 00:58:13,940
of course there are known tools out there

1495
00:58:13,940 --> 00:58:16,460
in the medical community and psychological community

1496
00:58:16,460 --> 00:58:18,700
for improving mood and mental health.

1497
00:58:18,700 --> 00:58:21,980
And while there are a variety of tools,

1498
00:58:21,980 --> 00:58:24,940
one of the main tools of the psychiatrist

1499
00:58:24,940 --> 00:58:26,780
is prescription drugs

1500
00:58:26,780 --> 00:58:29,700
that target specific neuromodulator systems

1501
00:58:29,700 --> 00:58:30,540
in the brain and body.

1502
00:58:30,540 --> 00:58:32,580
For instance, SSRI,

1503
00:58:32,580 --> 00:58:35,100
selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors

1504
00:58:35,100 --> 00:58:37,820
or atypical antidepressants

1505
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:40,620
that target the dopamine and epinephrine systems

1506
00:58:40,620 --> 00:58:42,660
such as wellbutrin, bupryorone

1507
00:58:42,660 --> 00:58:44,580
or other types of antidepressants.

1508
00:58:44,580 --> 00:58:48,460
Or for instance, nowadays there's a lot of growing excitement

1509
00:58:48,460 --> 00:58:52,660
about clinical trials using relatively high dosages

1510
00:58:52,660 --> 00:58:55,580
of psilocybin, which by the way,

1511
00:58:55,580 --> 00:58:58,860
closely mimics the chemical serotonin.

1512
00:58:58,860 --> 00:58:59,940
That's right, psilocybin,

1513
00:58:59,940 --> 00:59:03,060
which is converted to psilocin in the brain.

1514
00:59:03,060 --> 00:59:04,260
If you look at it chemically,

1515
00:59:04,260 --> 00:59:06,180
it looks very much like serotonin

1516
00:59:06,180 --> 00:59:08,420
although it has distinct effects from serotonin.

1517
00:59:08,420 --> 00:59:09,620
I talked about psilocybin

1518
00:59:09,620 --> 00:59:11,860
and what's being done in terms of the clinical trials,

1519
00:59:11,860 --> 00:59:13,660
safety considerations.

1520
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:15,860
I talked about the potential hazard considerations

1521
00:59:15,860 --> 00:59:17,940
and where the legality and all of that is going

1522
00:59:17,940 --> 00:59:20,220
in that episode if you want to check that out.

1523
00:59:20,220 --> 00:59:22,820
But the reason I'm taking a moment to mention these drugs,

1524
00:59:22,820 --> 00:59:26,060
things like SSRIs, Prozax, Olav, Citalopram,

1525
00:59:26,060 --> 00:59:29,060
wellbutrin, psilocybin and so on

1526
00:59:29,060 --> 00:59:33,180
is that all of them target specific neuromodulator systems

1527
00:59:33,180 --> 00:59:34,580
in the brain and body.

1528
00:59:34,580 --> 00:59:37,980
And at the same time, it's fairly clear

1529
00:59:38,020 --> 00:59:40,980
that mood disorders such as major depression

1530
00:59:40,980 --> 00:59:43,420
are not necessarily deficits

1531
00:59:43,420 --> 00:59:45,180
in things like serotonin or dopamine.

1532
00:59:45,180 --> 00:59:48,340
They can be, but most often they are not.

1533
00:59:48,340 --> 00:59:52,220
So why are such drugs prescribed for mood disorders

1534
00:59:52,220 --> 00:59:53,380
and for mental health disorders?

1535
00:59:53,380 --> 00:59:55,860
Well, because if specific neuromodulators

1536
00:59:55,860 --> 00:59:58,420
like serotonin, dopamine or epinephrine

1537
00:59:58,420 --> 01:00:01,900
are dramatically increased above baseline,

1538
01:00:01,900 --> 01:00:05,220
that affords the brain the ability to rewire itself.

1539
01:00:05,220 --> 01:00:08,060
Really the way to think about SSRIs

1540
01:00:08,060 --> 01:00:11,300
or atypical antidepressants or psilocybin

1541
01:00:11,300 --> 01:00:13,060
for the treatment of major depression

1542
01:00:14,020 --> 01:00:18,300
is really to think about them as chemical tools

1543
01:00:18,300 --> 01:00:21,260
to open or access neuroplasticity.

1544
01:00:21,260 --> 01:00:23,060
And that's why it's oh so important

1545
01:00:23,060 --> 01:00:25,500
that those drugs be combined with talk therapy

1546
01:00:25,500 --> 01:00:28,020
where people are actively working through the sources,

1547
01:00:28,020 --> 01:00:30,380
the real life sources and the historical sources,

1548
01:00:30,380 --> 01:00:33,460
maybe even the trauma-based sources of their depression.

1549
01:00:33,460 --> 01:00:36,660
And I mention this because there's a lot of debate nowadays

1550
01:00:36,660 --> 01:00:39,140
as to whether or not these drugs are useful,

1551
01:00:39,140 --> 01:00:42,140
whether or not the side effect profiles justify their use,

1552
01:00:42,140 --> 01:00:46,900
whether or not they are applicable to young populations.

1553
01:00:46,900 --> 01:00:48,180
There's a lot of debate about this.

1554
01:00:48,180 --> 01:00:51,220
And certainly in the case of the psychedelics,

1555
01:00:51,220 --> 01:00:53,140
there's a lot, a lot of debate

1556
01:00:53,140 --> 01:00:55,420
because this is a newly emerging area

1557
01:00:55,420 --> 01:00:56,860
and there's still not a lot of data,

1558
01:00:56,860 --> 01:01:00,060
although it's starting to increase over time.

1559
01:01:00,060 --> 01:01:03,460
But the key point here is that all of these drugs

1560
01:01:03,460 --> 01:01:06,420
have the potential to work in some people, not others.

1561
01:01:06,420 --> 01:01:08,500
Some people, they simply don't work for

1562
01:01:08,500 --> 01:01:12,380
and they cause more problems than solutions they solve,

