01:20:37,860 --> 01:20:40,320
And again, until those five minutes were completed.

2038
01:20:40,320 --> 01:20:42,660
Again, the outcome of that clinical trial

2039
01:20:42,660 --> 01:20:45,520
was that that particular pattern of breathing,

2040
01:20:45,520 --> 01:20:47,920
which we called cyclic physiological sighing

2041
01:20:47,920 --> 01:20:49,680
for five minutes per day,

2042
01:20:49,680 --> 01:20:51,880
again, done any time of day,

2043
01:20:51,880 --> 01:20:54,240
had the most positive outcomes

2044
01:20:54,240 --> 01:20:56,520
in terms of improving mood and mental health

2045
01:20:56,520 --> 01:20:57,660
and autonomic function,

2046
01:20:57,660 --> 01:21:00,560
those things related to sleep and heart rate variability.

2047
01:21:00,560 --> 01:21:04,140
So that's a very simple, very minimal time investment,

2048
01:21:04,140 --> 01:21:06,820
zero cost tool that anyone can use

2049
01:21:06,820 --> 01:21:10,200
that again improves various metrics of physical health,

2050
01:21:10,200 --> 01:21:12,640
but also improves metrics of mental health.

2051
01:21:12,640 --> 01:21:16,320
And it ties right back in with what was observed

2052
01:21:16,320 --> 01:21:19,480
in the work by Dr. Lisa Feldman Barrett,

2053
01:21:19,480 --> 01:21:24,260
exploring how putting more word label,

2054
01:21:24,260 --> 01:21:27,400
emotional granularity on one's emotional states

2055
01:21:27,400 --> 01:21:29,680
positively impact our physiological state.

2056
01:21:29,680 --> 01:21:31,400
And the fact that thinking about our emotions

2057
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:33,240
more frequently throughout the day

2058
01:21:33,240 --> 01:21:37,120
and deliberately putting more label granularity

2059
01:21:37,120 --> 01:21:40,720
on those emotions frequently throughout the day

2060
